name: Pinarayi Vijayan

Dear Shri. Sarbananda Sonowal Ji (@sarbanandsonwal), 

We are deeply saddened to learn about the Baghjan fire tragedy. We wish to assure you that the State of Kerala stands in solidarity with the people of Assam.

name: Pinarayi Vijayan
tweet: Kerala is a society that respects the outrage against injustice. If there is any silver lining in this, it is that we now know that we can make our voices heard against injustice. Let us be that people who fight injustice in all its forms; everytime, everywhere.

name: Pinarayi Vijayan
tweet: Having said that, we are saddened by the fact some have used this tragedy to unleash a hate campaign. Lies built upon inaccurate descriptions and half truths were employed to obliterate the truth. Some even tried to import bigotry into the narrative. Wrong priorities.

name: Pinarayi Vijayan

name: Pinarayi Vijayan
tweet: An investigation is underway, focusing on three suspects. The police and forest departments will jointly investigate the incident. The district police chief and the district forest officer visited the site today. We will do everything possible to bring the culprits to justice.

name: Pinarayi Vijayan
